SIMPLE: brisk
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brisk
<hw>Brisk</hw> <pr>(br⟦icr⟧sk)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. W.
<ets>brysg</ets>, fr. <ets>brys</ets> haste, Gael. <ets>briosg</ets>
quick, lively, Ir. <ets>broisg</ets> a start, leap, jerk.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of liveliness and activity; characterized by
quickness of motion or action; lively; spirited; quick.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Cheerily, boys; be <qex>brick</qex> awhile.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Brisk</qex> toil alternating with ready ease.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Full of spirit of life; effervescing, as liquors;
sparkling; <as>as, <ex>brick</ex> cider</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Active; lively; agile; alert; nimble; quick;
sprightly; vivacious; gay; spirited; animated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brisk</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Brisk
<hw>Brisk</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Bricked</conjf> <pr>(<?/)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Bricking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make or become
lively; to enliven; to animate; to take, or cause to take, an erect or
bold attitude; -- usually with <xex>up</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>brisken</ent>⟦br⟧
